¡Hi there!<br><br>I have already told you this (¡In person! (¡In Kyoto! How cool is that?)) but in case it helps others: I think love-loader is better-suited for implementing "an animation while loading resources". I don't think it will work for doing "dynamic loading", node.js-style, whithout heavy modifications. Nevertheless, you could use love-loader as a way to understand how threads work, and then do your own thing.<br><br>Regards!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=710">kikito</a> — Wed Aug 29, 2012 3:12 pm</p><hr />
