		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: love-loader: load resources in a separate thread, easily]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="https://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=48591#p48591"><![CDATA[
I had to make two changes to make it work, love-loader.lua:124 still used thread:send, and in main I replaced your quit with:<div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>  if key == 'escape' then   local f = love.event.quit or love.event.push  f("q")  end</code></pre></div>EDIT: Btw, love.event.quit doesn't take any arguments, but also ignores surplus ones, which is why this works. If you wonder why push("q") doesn't work any more, it's because events now have long names, so it's push("quit") instead.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=147">bartbes</a> — Thu Feb 02, 2012 5:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
